    <h3 class="subtitle">Tools:</h3>
    <p>Saw, Electric drill, Sandpaper, Hammer, Screwdriver, Ruler, Chisel, Wood clamps</p>

    <h3 class="subtitle">Materials:</h3>
    <p>Wood, Wood glue, Paint</p>

    <h3 class="subtitle">Steps:</h3>
    <ol>
        <li>1. Decide on the type and design of the furniture you wish to create. Draft a sketch and mark the dimensions.</li><li>2. Based on your design, measure and mark the necessary sections on the wood.</li><li>3. Use the saw to cut the wood based on your markings.</li><li>4. Use sandpaper to smooth all cut edges of the wood, ensuring there are no splinters.</li><li>5. Join the pieces together using nails, screws, and wood glue as per your design.</li><li>6. After assembly, sand the entire piece to ensure a smooth finish.</li><li>7. Apply varnish or paint to beautify and protect the furniture.</li>
    </ol>

